{"lemma":"نَصْبُ","slug":"نَصْبُ","root":"ن.ص.ب","root_slug":"ن-ص-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ص-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نَصْبُ","root":"نصب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":13,"pos_tags":["noun","prep","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":18},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39856","n39863","n39865","n39866","n39867","n39868"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to set up, to lay, to erect, to raise, to build","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"نَصَبَ نَفْسَهُ لِشَيْءٍ","english":"to dedicate oneself to something"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to raise the vowel to /a/; to put into the accusative case","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to raise the vowel to /a/; to put into the subjunctive mood","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to proclaim, to declare, to arrogate to oneself (king, war, sovereignty …)","tags":["ditransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to concern, to be directed at, to focus on, to concentrate on","tags":["formal","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to swindle, to scam, to ambush","tags":["informal","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to appoint, to assign","examples":[{"text":"نَصَبَ نَفْسَهُ مَلِكًا","english":"he proclaimed himself king"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strive, to labor, to toil","examples":[{"text":"فَإِذَا فَرَغْتَ فَٱنْصَبْ\n وَإِلَىٰ رَبِّكَ فَٱرْغَب","english":"So when thou art free [from thy tasks], then strive [in worship]. And toward thy Lord and Master turn [thy] attention."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to install, to establish","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"عِنْدَمَا نَصَّبْتَ اَلْبَرْنَامَجَ، هَلْ أَنْشَأْتَ لَهُ كَلِمَةِ سِرّ؟","english":"When you installed the program did you set up a password?"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to appoint, to assign"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَصَبَ (naṣaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"accusative case","tags":["accusative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"subjunctive mood"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"swindle, trickery, deception, fraud","tags":["colloquial"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an array of stones or a structure set up as a sign or mark to show the way (especially in the desert)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"something erected, sculpture, statue, monument","examples":[{"text":"[…]إِنَّمَا الْخَمْرُ وَٱلْمَيْسِرُ وَٱلْأَنْصَابُ وَٱلْأَزْلَامُ رِجْسٌ مِنْ عَمَلِ الشَّيْطَانِ فَٱجْتَنِبُوهُ[…]","english":"[…] Wine/liquor and games of chance/gambling and [sacrificing upon or offering unto] stone altars/statues and [drawing or casting] divination arrows are surely an abomination, of Satan's handiwork, so shun it […]"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"something erected, sculpture, statue, monument","examples":[{"text":"حُرِّمَتْ عَلَيْكُمُ الْمَيْتَةُ وَالدَّمُ[…]وَمَا ذُبِحَ عَلَى النُّصُب[…]","english":"And prohibited unto you are carrion/dead meat and blood […] and what was slain upon the stone altars/statues […]"}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"in front of"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39856","headword_ar":"نَصَبَ","root":"nSb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nS~b","text_ar":"نصّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He set up, put up, set upright, erected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing: (S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he elevated, raised, reared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing. (K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He set up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a stone"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba raA^osahu","text_ar":"نَصَبَ رَاْسَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He raised his head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSiba","text_ar":"نَصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSabN","text_ar":"نَصَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a goat)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had erect ears."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S: the inf. n. only mentioned.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSabotu fulAanFA lika*aA","text_ar":"نَصَبْتُ فُلاَنًا لِكَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I set,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"set up, such a one as an obstacle to such a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a butt for such a thing, like the butt of archers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ErD","text_ar":"عرض"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSiba fulaAnN liEimaArapi Albaladi","text_ar":"نُصِبَ فُلَانٌ لِعِمَارَةِ البَلَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one was set up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appointed, for the putting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keeping, of the town,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"district, in a flourishing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosperous state, with respect to building, culture, population, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba","text_ar":"نَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba naSoba AlEarabi","text_ar":"نَصَبَ نَصْبَ العَرَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sang,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chanted, a kind of song,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chant, peculiar to the Arabs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, &c.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the description termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HudaA'","text_ar":"حُدَاء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by which camels are urged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of song"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling what is thus termed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but finer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more delicate."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) What is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of singing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chanting, above described:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HudaA'","text_ar":"حُدَاء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling singing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of modulation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of song,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chant, of the Arabs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Arabs of the desert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poetry such as is commonly recited, well regulated and set to an air:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so called because, in"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"singing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chanting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, the voice is raised,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(The Fáïk.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba AlHarofa","text_ar":"نَصَبَ الحَرْفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (not"},{"kind":"text","text":",) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He wrote,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pronounced, the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"letter with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSob","text_ar":"نَصْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is, in the case of the final inflection of a word, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatoH","text_ar":"فَتْح"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the non-inflection:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. e., he wrote it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pronounced it, with"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"text","text":":) so called because the sound of a word of which the final letter is so pronounced rises to the highest cavity of the mouth. (Lth.) A conv. term of grammar. (S, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba Alkalimapa","text_ar":"نَصَبَ الكَلِمَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He wrote,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pronounced, the word with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSob","text_ar":"نَصْب"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. e., making its vowel of inflection"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"according to the rules of grammar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made the word to have fet-hah as its vowel of inflection."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba lah AlHaroba","text_ar":"نَصَبَ لَه الحَرْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made war upon him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waDaEa","text_ar":"وَضَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b10-  Of anything that is raised, and with which one goes to meet, or encounter, a thing, one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSiba","text_ar":"نُصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and of the agent,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba","text_ar":"نَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba lahu","text_ar":"نَصَبَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He acted with hostility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enmity, towards him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) See also 3. ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSabotu lahu raA^oyFA","text_ar":"نَصَبْتُ لَهُ رَاْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave him counsel from which he should not deviate."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba","text_ar":"نَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put down"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing: syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waDaEa","text_ar":"وَضَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Thus the verb bears two contr. significations. (K.) ―         -b14-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He set,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put,"},{"kind":"text","text":"absolutely: often used in this sense.] ―         -b15-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSabahu","text_ar":"نَصَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnSbh","text_ar":"انصبه","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inoSaAbN","text_ar":"اـِنْصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(disease)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pained him; occasioned him pain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b16-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba Als~ayora","text_ar":"نَصَبَ السَّيْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He strove,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exerted himself, unusually in his pace:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba","text_ar":"نَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he pursued his journey with diligence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"energy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he travelled on all the day, at a gentle pace:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he journeyed on all the night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) En-Nadr says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aSobu","text_ar":"النَّصْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the first pace; then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ababu","text_ar":"الدَّبَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasaja","text_ar":"وَسَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEanaqu","text_ar":"العَنَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~azay~udu","text_ar":"التَّزَيُّدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEasoju","text_ar":"العَسْجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~atoku","text_ar":"الرَّتْكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwaxodu","text_ar":"الوَخْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alhamolajapu","text_ar":"الهَمْلَجَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSiba","text_ar":"نَصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSabN","text_ar":"نَصَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was fatigued, tired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wearied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSiba","text_ar":"نَصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSabN","text_ar":"نَصَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He suffered difficulty, trouble, distress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affliction."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSiba","text_ar":"نَصِبَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He strove; laboured;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"toiled."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA_i*aA faragota faA@noSabo","text_ar":"فَاـِذَا فَرَغْتَ فَا@نْصَبْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[Kur, xciv. 7,] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And when thou shalt have finished"},{"kind":"text","text":"thy prescribed prayers,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigue thyself"},{"kind":"text","text":"in supplication: (Katádeh, Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when thou shalt have finished"},{"kind":"text","text":"the obligatory prayers,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigue thyself"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the performance of the voluntary. (TA.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASibN","text_ar":"نَاصِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K","AA","Sh","ISd","TA","Nh"]},{"entry_id":"n39863","headword_ar":"نَصْبٌ","root":"nSb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba","text_ar":"نَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (of which it is the inf. n.,) throughout. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba","text_ar":"نَصَبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSubN","text_ar":"نُصُبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSiybapN","text_ar":"نَصِيبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark, set up to show the way;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a standard set up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalamN manoSuwbN","text_ar":"عَلَمٌ مَنْصُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. e., set up"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a sign"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSubN","text_ar":"نُصُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSiybapN","text_ar":"نَصِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sufunN","text_ar":"سُفُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safiynapN","text_ar":"سَفِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth, TA.) Also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSobapN","text_ar":"نُصْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pole,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mast;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAriyapN","text_ar":"سَارِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"set up to show the way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaASiybu","text_ar":"اَنَاصِيبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanaASiybu","text_ar":"تَنَاصِيبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(pls. which have no sings., TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Signs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones, set up to show the way;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolaAmN","text_ar":"اَعْلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuwFY","text_ar":"صُوًى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones set up on the tops of isolated small mountains, whereby travellers are to be directed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanoSuwbN","text_ar":"يَنْصُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanaASiybu","text_ar":"يَنَاصِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark, set up to show the way in a desert."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr.) In the Kur, lxx., last verse but one, some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobK","text_ar":"نَصْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning as above: others"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSubK","text_ar":"نُصُبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning “ idols. ” (Zj.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A goal;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAyapN","text_ar":"غَايَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or rather, some say that"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2800},{"kind":"text","text":"it has this signification [in the verse of the Kur. above referred to]; but the former meaning, of “ a sign, &c., ” is the more correct. (TA.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSobN","text_ar":"نُصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSubN","text_ar":"نُصُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below. ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with respect to rhyme in a verse, is The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being free from anything that would mar it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Akh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the verse itself is not curtailed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for when the verse is curtailed, the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nSb","text_ar":"نصب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not applicable, though the rhyme be perfect: accord. to an explanation received from the Arabs: not one of the terms of Kh. (Akh.) Derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAinotiSaAbu","text_ar":"الاِنْتِصَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as signifying “ the standing erect; being tall; making one's self tall, by stretching the neck; ” and therefore not applied to verse that is curtailed. (IJ, ISd.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who is set,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"set up, as an obstacle"},{"kind":"text","text":"to a thing, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a butt"},{"kind":"text","text":"for a thing,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the butt of archers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ErD","text_ar":"عرض"},{"kind":"text","text":".) See 1. ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A peculiar mode of singing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chanting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a peculiar kind of song,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (See 1.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Akh"]},{"entry_id":"n39865","headword_ar":"نِصْبٌ","root":"nSb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSiybN","text_ar":"نَصِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n39866","headword_ar":"نَصَبٌ","root":"nSb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[as a subst.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fatigue; weariness; toil."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Difficulty; trouble; distress; affliction."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See the verb: and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n39867","headword_ar":"نَصِبٌ","root":"nSb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Diseased; sick; and in pain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n39868","headword_ar":"نُصُبٌ","root":"nSb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSubN","text_ar":"نُصُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, Msb) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSobN","text_ar":"نُصْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K: accord. to the S, the latter is sometimes written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSubN","text_ar":"نُصُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [but it seems that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSubN","text_ar":"نُصُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the more common of the two words:]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is set up and worshipped to the exclusion of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in preference to, the true God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that is so worshipped:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stone that is set up and so worshipped:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSubN","text_ar":"نُصُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoSaAbN","text_ar":"اَنْصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSubN","text_ar":"نُصُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suqufN","text_ar":"سُقُفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqofN","text_ar":"سَقْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or it is a pl. of which the sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niSaAbN","text_ar":"نِصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and it may be a sing., the pl. of which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoSaAbN","text_ar":"اَنْصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Zj:) which last word, accord. to some, is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSonaAmN","text_ar":"اَصْنَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but others deny this; because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASnAm","text_ar":"اصنام"},{"kind":"text","text":"are figured and sculptured or painted; whereas"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnSAb","text_ar":"انصاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"are of an opposite description. (Msb.) [See a verse cited in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mwr","text_ar":"مور"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  Also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^anoSaAbu","text_ar":"الاَنْصَابُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain stones which were set up around the Kaabeh, over which it was customary for the name of some deity to be pronounced in the killing of animals"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuhal~u EalayohaA","text_ar":"يُهَلُّ عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and upon which victims were slain in sacrifice to another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"others, than the true God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K:) pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSubN","text_ar":"نُصُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonaAqN","text_ar":"اَعْنَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuqN","text_ar":"عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSobq","text_ar":"نُصْبق"},{"kind":"text","text":", as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqofaAlN","text_ar":"اَقْفَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qufolN","text_ar":"قُفْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSubN","text_ar":"نُصُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as occurring in the Kur, v. 4, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An idol;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stone which the pagan Arabs set up, to sacrifice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slay animals, before it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by it, and which became red with the blood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kt:) or pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niSaAbN","text_ar":"نِصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"idols."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoSaAbu AlHarami","text_ar":"اَنْصَابُ الحَرَمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The limits of the sacred territory"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Mekkeh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. e., signs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marks, set up there, whereby it might be known."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSobN","text_ar":"نَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K","Msb","S","Zj","ISd","Kt"]}]}}